        <div n="136-31A7" type="poem"><head type="note" n="1" xml:id="spp-136-31A7-headnote-1"><lg n="1" xml:id="spp-136-31A7-headnote-1-line-group-1" type="headnote"><l n="1" xml:id="spp-136-31A7-headnote-1-line-group-1-line-1"/></lg></head><head type="note" n="2" xml:id="spp-136-31A7-headnote-2"><lg n="1" xml:id="spp-136-31A7-headnote-2-line-group-1" type="headnote"><l n="1" xml:id="spp-136-31A7-headnote-2-line-group-1-line-1"/></lg></head><head type="note" n="3" xml:id="spp-136-31A7-headnote-3"><lg n="1" xml:id="spp-136-31A7-headnote-3-line-group-1" type="headnote"><l n="1" xml:id="spp-136-31A7-headnote-3-line-group-1-line-1"/></lg></head>
      <lg n="1" type="triplet"><l n="1" xml:id="spp-136-31A7-line-1"><gap/><gap/><gap/><gap/><gap/><gap/><gap/><gap/><gap/><gap/><gap/><gap/><gap/><gap/><gap/><gap/><gap/><gap/><gap/><gap/><gap/><gap/><gap/><gap/><gap/><gap/><gap/><gap/><gap/><gap/> Now in contiguous Drops the Flood comes down,&#13;</l><l n="2" xml:id="spp-136-31A7-line-2"> Threat'ning with Deluge this Devoted Town:</l><l n="3" xml:id="spp-136-31A7-line-3"> To Shops in Crowds the daggled Females fly,</l><l n="4" xml:id="spp-136-31A7-line-4"> Pretend to cheapen Goods but nothing buy.<gap/><gap/><gap/><gap/><gap/><gap/><gap/><gap/><gap/><gap/><gap/><gap/><gap/><gap/><gap/><gap/><gap/><gap/></l><l n="5" xml:id="spp-136-31A7-line-5"> Now from all Parts the swelling Kennels flow,</l><l n="6" xml:id="spp-136-31A7-line-6"> And bear their Trophies with them as they go:</l><l n="7" xml:id="spp-136-31A7-line-7"> Filth of all Hues and Odors seem to tell</l><l n="8" xml:id="spp-136-31A7-line-8"> What Street they sail'd from, by their sight &amp; smell.</l><l n="9" xml:id="spp-136-31A7-line-9"> They, as each Torrent drives, with rapid Force</l><l n="10" xml:id="spp-136-31A7-line-10"> From Smithfield or S<hi rend="sup">tÌ£</hi> 'Pulchre's shape their Course,</l><l n="11" xml:id="spp-136-31A7-line-11"> And in huge Confluent join'd at Snow-hill Ridge,</l><l n="12" xml:id="spp-136-31A7-line-12"> Fall from the Conduit prone to Holborn-Bridge.</l><l n="13" xml:id="spp-136-31A7-line-13"> Sweepings from Butchers Stalls, Dung, Guts &amp; Blood,</l><l n="14" xml:id="spp-136-31A7-line-14"> Drown'd Puppies, stinking Sprats, all drench'd in Mud,</l><l n="15" xml:id="spp-136-31A7-line-15"> Dead Cats &amp; Turnep-Tops come tumbling down y<hi rend="sup">e</hi> flood.136-31A7   </l></lg></div>
